udit every quarter. Remove toxic links and identify new opportunities. What to Avoid: ABA-Compliant Link Practices ABA Model Rule 7.2 governs communications about legal services. Several common link building tactics cross ethical lines for attorneys. Do not: - Buy links from private blog networks (PBNs) - Exchange links with other law firms in a reciprocal scheme - Use testimonials that imply guaranteed outcomes - Publish misleading specialization claims to earn links - Pay for editorial links disguised as organic content Safe alternatives: - Earn links through original research and data - Provide expert commentary to journalists (HARO, Connectively) - Publish genuine case studies with client consent - Create free community resources that attract natural links Chapter 7: Technical SEO Checklist for Law Firms A slow, poorly structured website will not rank regardless of how good your content is. Technical SEO ensures Google can crawl, index, and understand your site. Core Web Vitals for Law Firm Websites Google uses Core Web Vitals as a ranking signal. These 3 metrics measure user experience. Metric What It Measures Target LCP (Largest Contentful Paint) Page load speed Under 2.5 seconds INP (Interaction to Next Paint) Responsiveness Under 200 milliseconds CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift) Visual stability Under 0.1 Common issues on law firm websites: Oversized hero images that slow LCP Unoptimized third-party scripts (live chat widgets, analytics) Missing image dimensions that cause layout shifts Heavy custom fonts that block rendering Run your site through Google PageSpeed Insights. Fix the top 3 issues first. Most law firm websites can reach passing scores with image compression and script deferral alone. Schema Markup for Legal Services Schema markup helps Google understand your content and display rich results. Law firms should implement these schema types. Schema Type Use Case Benefit LocalBusiness (LegalService) Homepage and contact page Map Pack eligibility, rich 