maining clicks. The firms that ignore AI search will see traffic decline steadily. How to Get Cited in AI-Generated Answers AI Overviews pull content from pages that Google considers authoritative on the topic. Getting cited in these summaries requires a specific content approach. Read our full Generative Engine Optimization guide for the complete strategy. Here are the key tactics for law firms. Structure content for extraction. Use clear H2 and H3 headers. Write concise definitions and explanations in the first paragraph under each header. AI models pull from well-structured content. Include specific data and statistics. AI summaries prefer content with concrete numbers. "The average car accident settlement in Texas is $15,000 to $75,000" is more citable than "settlements vary." Build entity authority. Consistent author bylines, schema markup, and cross-platform presence (Avvo, LinkedIn, publications) establish your attorneys as recognized entities. Answer the exact question. Match your H2 headers to common search queries. Start the section with a direct answer, then expand. Our guide on optimizing for AI Overviews covers the tactical details. The Zero-Click Problem for Attorneys Zero-click searches are queries where the user gets their answer without clicking any result. For law firms, this means potential clients may read a summary of their legal rights, average settlement amounts, or legal processes without ever reaching your website. The counter-strategy has 3 parts: Target queries that require action. "Personal injury lawyer near me" cannot be fully answered by an AI Overview. The searcher still needs to call someone. Create content that goes deeper than a summary. AI Overviews provide surface-level answers. Your content should offer state-specific detail, case examples, and actionable next steps. Build brand recognition. When your firm appears in AI Overviews repeatedly, searchers remember the name. Direct searches for your firm name bypass AI Overviews enti